<br />so the trick is:
<br />* pick up the Hue/Saturation/Value value from the actual VRAM's palette using the color bits/index taken from tile data and attribute table
<br />* fetch the upper 3 bits from PPU $2001
<br />* fetch the corrisponding entry of that array above using that 3 bits
<br />* multiply the this last value fetched by each one of the 3 values of the array's entry
<br />* ...finally i'll have 3 values: one for red, another for green and another for blue (in that order). is it correct?
